== 8...e5 · Carlsbad variation ==
Black finally pushes the e pawn forward, releasing the dark-squared bishop and fighting for the center. 

If White ignores the pawn and prepares to castle with 9. Bg2, Black can start building pressure with 9...Rd8, aiming at White's queen, and 10...Be6 pressuring the knight (if 9...O-O-O then 10. a5! followed by 11. Qa4 starts a nasty attack on the queenside).

Therefore, White's best option is [[/9. dxe5|'''9. dxe5''']], exchanging pawns in the center.

=== History ===
The Carlsbad variation is likely named after the tournament with the move's first appearance, that being the Karlsbad tournament from 1929. It was featured in a game between Capablanca and Vidmar<ref>https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1066826</ref>.


